## 1. **Subset Sum Problem (Partition Equal Subset Sum - Leetcode 416)**

**Instinct:**  
Array ko do subsets me divide karna hai with equal sum. Means total sum even hona chahiye aur target = sum/2 achieve karna hai. Har element ya toh lo ya mat lo.

**Approach:**  
1. Total sum calculate karo, agar odd hai toh false
2. target = sum/2
3. Memo[i][target] = kya index i se target achieve kar sakte ho
4. Base: target == 0 → true; i == n → false
5. Ya toh lo (target - nums[i]) ya mat lo

```java
class Solution {
    int[] nums;
    int n;
    Boolean[][] memo;
    
    public boolean canPartition(int[] nums) {
        this.nums = nums;
        n = nums.length;
        int sum = 0;
        for (int num : nums) sum += num;
        if (sum % 2 != 0) return false;
        
        int target = sum / 2;
        memo = new Boolean[n][target + 1];
        return dfs(0, target);
    }
    
    private boolean dfs(int i, int target) {
        if (target == 0) return true;
        if (i >= n || target < 0) return false;
        if (memo[i][target] != null) return memo[i][target];
        
        boolean take = dfs(i + 1, target - nums[i]);
        boolean skip = dfs(i + 1, target);
        
        memo[i][target] = take || skip;
        return memo[i][target];
    }
}
```

**Key Insight:** Classic subset sum - 0/1 knapsack style. Existence check.

