## 2. **Count Subsets with Given Sum**

**Instinct:**  
Kitne subsets ka sum exactly target ke equal hai. Har element ya toh lo ya mat lo, count add karo.

**Approach:**  
1. Memo[i][target] = number of subsets from index i with given target
2. Base: target == 0 → 1; i == n → 0
3. take + skip (if target >= nums[i])

```java
class Solution {
    int[] nums;
    int n;
    Integer[][] memo;
    
    public int countSubsetsWithSum(int[] nums, int target) {
        this.nums = nums;
        n = nums.length;
        memo = new Integer[n][target + 1];
        return dfs(0, target);
    }
    
    private int dfs(int i, int target) {
        if (target == 0) return 1;
        if (i >= n || target < 0) return 0;
        if (memo[i][target] != null) return memo[i][target];
        
        int take = dfs(i + 1, target - nums[i]);
        int skip = dfs(i + 1, target);
        
        memo[i][target] = take + skip;
        return memo[i][target];
    }
}
```

**Key Insight:** Count subsets = sum of take and skip. Base case when target becomes 0.

