## 4. **Minimum Subset Sum Difference**

**Instinct:**  
Array ko do subsets me divide karna hai such that sum difference minimum ho. Target = sum/2 ke nearest sum find karo. Answer = sum - 2 * best.

**Approach:**  
1. total sum calculate karo
2. target = sum/2
3. Find max subset sum <= target
4. Answer = sum - 2 * maxSum

```java
class Solution {
    int[] nums;
    int n;
    Integer[][] memo;
    
    public int minSubsetSumDifference(int[] nums) {
        this.nums = nums;
        n = nums.length;
        int sum = 0;
        for (int num : nums) sum += num;
        
        int target = sum / 2;
        memo = new Integer[n][target + 1];
        int maxSum = dfs(0, target);
        return sum - 2 * maxSum;
    }
    
    private int dfs(int i, int capacity) {
        if (i >= n || capacity <= 0) return 0;
        if (memo[i][capacity] != null) return memo[i][capacity];
        
        int skip = dfs(i + 1, capacity);
        int take = 0;
        if (nums[i] <= capacity) {
            take = nums[i] + dfs(i + 1, capacity - nums[i]);
        }
        
        memo[i][capacity] = Math.max(skip, take);
        return memo[i][capacity];
    }
}
```

**Key Insight:** Minimize difference = find subset closest to sum/2.

