## 5. **Largest Divisible Subset (Leetcode 368)**

**Instinct:**  
Subset where for every pair (a,b), a % b == 0 or b % a == 0. Sort array, then for each i, find largest subset ending at i where nums[i] % nums[j] == 0.

**Approach:**  
1. Sort array
2. Memo[i] = largest divisible subset ending at i
3. For each j < i, if nums[i] % nums[j] == 0, update

```java
class Solution {
    int[] nums;
    int n;
    List<Integer>[] memo;
    
    public List<Integer> largestDivisibleSubset(int[] nums) {
        this.nums = nums;
        n = nums.length;
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        memo = new List[n];
        
        List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            List<Integer> subset = dfs(i);
            if (subset.size() > result.size()) {
                result = subset;
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
    
    private List<Integer> dfs(int i) {
        if (memo[i] != null) return memo[i];
        
        List<Integer> best = new ArrayList<>();
        best.add(nums[i]);
        
        for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
            if (nums[i] % nums[j] == 0) {
                List<Integer> candidate = new ArrayList<>(dfs(j));
                if (candidate.size() + 1 > best.size()) {
                    best = new ArrayList<>(candidate);
                    best.add(nums[i]);
                }
            }
        }
        
        memo[i] = best;
        return best;
    }
}
```

**Key Insight:** Sort + DP. Divisible property is transitive when sorted.

