## 6. **Longest Increasing Subsequence (Leetcode 300) - Subsequence**

**Instinct:**  
Array me longest strictly increasing subsequence. Har element ya toh sequence me lo (if greater than previous) ya skip.

**Approach:**  
1. Memo[i][prev] = LIS length from i with previous index prev
2. Base: i == n → 0
3. skip or take (if prev == -1 or nums[i] > nums[prev])

```java
class Solution {
    int[] nums;
    int n;
    Integer[][] memo;
    
    public int lengthOfLIS(int[] nums) {
        this.nums = nums;
        n = nums.length;
        memo = new Integer[n][n + 1];
        return dfs(0, -1);
    }
    
    private int dfs(int i, int prev) {
        if (i == n) return 0;
        int prevIdx = prev + 1;
        if (memo[i][prevIdx] != null) return memo[i][prevIdx];
        
        int skip = dfs(i + 1, prev);
        int take = 0;
        if (prev == -1 || nums[i] > nums[prev]) {
            take = 1 + dfs(i + 1, i);
        }
        
        memo[i][prevIdx] = Math.max(skip, take);
        return memo[i][prevIdx];
    }
}
```

**Key Insight:** Classic LIS - pick/skip with previous index tracking.

