## 8. **Maximum Sum Increasing Subsequence**

**Instinct:**  
Length ki jagah sum maximize karna hai. Same LIS logic, but sum add karo, length nahi.

**Approach:**  
1. Memo[i] = max sum increasing subsequence ending at i
2. For each j < i where nums[j] < nums[i]
3. maxSum = max(maxSum, nums[i] + memo[j])

```java
class Solution {
    int[] nums;
    int n;
    Integer[] memo;
    
    public int maxSumIS(int[] nums) {
        this.nums = nums;
        n = nums.length;
        memo = new Integer[n];
        
        int maxSum = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, dfs(i));
        }
        return maxSum;
    }
    
    private int dfs(int i) {
        if (memo[i] != null) return memo[i];
        
        int max = nums[i];
        for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
            if (nums[j] < nums[i]) {
                max = Math.max(max, nums[i] + dfs(j));
            }
        }
        
        memo[i] = max;
        return max;
    }
}
```

**Key Insight:** Sum LIS - same structure, different aggregation.

