## 11. **Longest Arithmetic Subsequence (Leetcode 1027)**

**Instinct:**  
Array me longest arithmetic subsequence (difference constant). Har index ke liye, difference track karo.

**Approach:**  
1. Memo[i][diff] = max length ending at i with given diff
2. For each j < i, diff = nums[i] - nums[j]
3. length = memo[j][diff] + 1

```java
class Solution {
    int[] nums;
    int n;
    Map<Integer, Integer>[] memo;
    
    public int longestArithSeqLength(int[] nums) {
        this.nums = nums;
        n = nums.length;
        memo = new Map[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            memo[i] = new HashMap<>();
        }
        
        int maxLen = 1;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, dfs(i));
        }
        return maxLen;
    }
    
    private int dfs(int i) {
        int max = 1;
        for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
            int diff = nums[i] - nums[j];
            int len = memo[j].getOrDefault(diff, 1) + 1;
            memo[i].put(diff, Math.max(memo[i].getOrDefault(diff, 1), len));
            max = Math.max(max, len);
        }
        return max;
    }
}
```

**Key Insight:** Diff based DP. Use Map for diff → length.

