## 15. **Number of Subsequences with XOR K**

**Instinct:**  
Subsequences count where XOR of elements equals K. State = (index, xor).

**Approach:**  
1. Memo[i][xor] = count from i with current xor value
2. take: xor ^ nums[i]
3. skip: same xor

```java
class Solution {
    int MOD = 1_000_000_007;
    int[] nums;
    int k;
    int[][] memo;
    
    public int countSubsequencesWithXOR(int[] nums, int k) {
        this.nums = nums;
        this.k = k;
        int n = nums.length;
        memo = new int[n][1024]; // assuming max XOR value < 1024
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            Arrays.fill(memo[i], -1);
        }
        return dfs(0, 0);
    }
    
    private int dfs(int i, int xor) {
        if (i == nums.length) return xor == k ? 1 : 0;
        if (memo[i][xor] != -1) return memo[i][xor];
        
        int skip = dfs(i + 1, xor);
        int take = dfs(i + 1, xor ^ nums[i]);
        
        memo[i][xor] = (skip + take) % MOD;
        return memo[i][xor];
    }
}
```

**Key Insight:** XOR operation in state. Track current XOR value.

