## 17. **Number of Subsequences with OR K**

**Instinct:**  
Subsequences count where OR of elements equals K. State = (index, or). OR only increases.

**Approach:**  
1. Memo[i][or] = count from i with current OR value
2. take: or | nums[i]
3. skip: same OR

```java
class Solution {
    int MOD = 1_000_000_007;
    int[] nums;
    int k;
    int[][] memo;
    
    public int countSubsequencesWithOR(int[] nums, int k) {
        this.nums = nums;
        this.k = k;
        int n = nums.length;
        memo = new int[n][k + 1];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            Arrays.fill(memo[i], -1);
        }
        return dfs(0, 0);
    }
    
    private int dfs(int i, int or) {
        if (i == nums.length) return or == k ? 1 : 0;
        if (or > k) return 0; // OR can't decrease, so prune
        if (memo[i][or] != -1) return memo[i][or];
        
        int skip = dfs(i + 1, or);
        int take = dfs(i + 1, or | nums[i]);
        
        memo[i][or] = (skip + take) % MOD;
        return memo[i][or];
    }
}
```

**Key Insight:** OR only increases. Prune when OR exceeds K.

