## 18. **Longest String Chain (Leetcode 1048)**

**Instinct:**  
Strings ki chain where next string = previous + 1 character. Sort by length, then LIS with predecessor check.

**Approach:**  
1. Sort by length
2. Memo[i][prev] = max chain length
3. Check if prev is predecessor of current

```java
class Solution {
    String[] words;
    int n;
    Integer[][] memo;
    
    public int longestStrChain(String[] words) {
        this.words = words;
        n = words.length;
        Arrays.sort(words, (a, b) -> a.length() - b.length());
        memo = new Integer[n][n + 1];
        return dfs(0, -1);
    }
    
    private int dfs(int i, int prev) {
        if (i == n) return 0;
        int prevIdx = prev + 1;
        if (memo[i][prevIdx] != null) return memo[i][prevIdx];
        
        int skip = dfs(i + 1, prev);
        int take = 0;
        if (prev == -1 || isPredecessor(words[prev], words[i])) {
            take = 1 + dfs(i + 1, i);
        }
        
        memo[i][prevIdx] = Math.max(skip, take);
        return memo[i][prevIdx];
    }
    
    private boolean isPredecessor(String a, String b) {
        if (b.length() != a.length() + 1) return false;
        int i = 0, j = 0;
        while (i < a.length() && j < b.length()) {
            if (a.charAt(i) == b.charAt(j)) i++;
            j++;
        }
        return i == a.length();
    }
}
```

**Key Insight:** Sort by length. Predecessor check removes exactly one character.

