## 19. **Number of Subsequences of String A that Form String B**

**Instinct:**  
String A ke kitne subsequences exactly string B ke equal hain. Classic subsequence matching DP.

**Approach:**  
1. Memo[i][j] = ways to form B[j..] from A[i..]
2. If j == B.length() → 1
3. If i == A.length() → 0
4. If A[i] == B[j] → take + skip
5. Else → skip

```java
class Solution {
    String A, B;
    int[][] memo;
    int MOD = 1_000_000_007;
    
    public int numSubsequences(String A, String B) {
        this.A = A;
        this.B = B;
        int n = A.length(), m = B.length();
        memo = new int[n][m];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            Arrays.fill(memo[i], -1);
        }
        return dfs(0, 0);
    }
    
    private int dfs(int i, int j) {
        if (j == B.length()) return 1;
        if (i == A.length()) return 0;
        if (memo[i][j] != -1) return memo[i][j];
        
        int ways = dfs(i + 1, j); // skip
        
        if (A.charAt(i) == B.charAt(j)) {
            ways = (ways + dfs(i + 1, j + 1)) % MOD; // take
        }
        
        memo[i][j] = ways;
        return ways;
    }
}
```

**Key Insight:** String matching subsequence count. Take only when chars match.

