## 20. **Maximum Number of Ways to Partition Array into Subsequences**

**Instinct:**  
Array ko subsequences me partition karna hai with constraints. State = (index, last element of each subsequence).

**Approach:**  
1. Memo[i][last1][last2]... but too many states
2. Better: Greedy with map tracking last elements

```java
class Solution {
    public int maxNumOfSubsequences(int[] nums, int k) {
        // Greedy: put each number in a subsequence where it fits
        Map<Integer, Integer> last = new HashMap<>();
        int count = 0;
        
        for (int num : nums) {
            boolean placed = false;
            for (int prev = num - k; prev <= num + k; prev++) {
                if (last.containsKey(prev)) {
                    int freq = last.get(prev);
                    if (freq == 1) {
                        last.remove(prev);
                    } else {
                        last.put(prev, freq - 1);
                    }
                    last.put(num, last.getOrDefault(num, 0) + 1);
                    placed = true;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if (!placed) {
                last.put(num, last.getOrDefault(num, 0) + 1);
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```

**Key Insight:** Greedy assignment to existing subsequences when possible.

